cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 

- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the theoretical underpinnings of a logical framework for Integer Linear Programming.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses optimization procedures for linear constraints and optimization, which are common in operations research and software verification.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is another possible category as the paper deals with Integer Linear Programming, which is a topic in discrete mathematics.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper discusses the application of the IMT approach to industrial synthesis and design problems, which are common in AI.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper discusses real-time constraints arising in the development of the Boeing 787, which is a topic in systems and control.
